# Server actions and data layer

## Server actions

- Place in `src/app/actions.ts` (main) or `src/app/totp-actions.ts` (auth/TOTP only).
- Start file with `"use server"`.
- Name: `*Action` (e.g. `createProjectAction`, `updateProjectAction`).
- Start with `requireUser()` or `requireAdmin()`; redirect admins from user flows when applicable.
- After mutations: `revalidatePath(...)` and often `redirect(...)` with query params for flash messages (e.g. `?tab=team&member_added=...`).
- Read `FormData` in actions; validate and trim strings; parse numbers like budget with `parseInt(...replace(/\D/g, ""), 10)`.

## Project access

Use `src/lib/project-data.ts`:

- `getProjectForUser`, `getProjectMetaForUser`, `getApartmentForUser`
- `assertProjectAccess`, `assertApartmentAccess`
- `seedProjectCriteria`, `apartmentScore`, `flattenCriteria`

Do not query projects without a membership check.

## Prisma

- Single client: `src/lib/prisma.ts`.
- Schema changes: edit `prisma/schema.prisma`, then `npm run db:push` (no migration files in routine dev).
- Cascade deletes are defined on relations; deleting a project removes members, apartments, criteria.

## API routes

- `src/app/api/admin/backup/` — admin-only ZIP export/import
- `src/app/api/projects/[projectId]/calendar.ics` — token auth via `icalToken`
- `src/app/api/projects/[projectId]/geocode` — geocoding
- `src/app/uploads/[...path]/route.ts` — serve files from data dir

## Lib modules (extend, do not duplicate)

| Module | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `scoring.ts` | Weights, dealbreakers, `formatPrice`, score math |
| `viewings.ts` | Viewing dates, `nextViewing` |
| `defaults.ts` | Default criterion groups for new projects |
| `backup.ts` | Admin ZIP backup (DB + uploads) |
| `totp.ts` | TOTP secret, QR, recovery codes |
| `ical.ts` / `ical-token.ts` | Calendar feed |
| `geocode.ts` | Address → coordinates |

## Backups

- Use `adm-zip` (not `archiver`) for Next.js compatibility.
- Raw SQL via `$queryRawUnsafe` when needed for SQLite pragmas during export.
